    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName ref="#eutychis"><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1876b #bertolini1877 #cilv8687">Cicria Euty</supplied>chidi</persName>.
                    <lb n="2"/><persName ref="#heracleon">Cicrius Heracleon</persName>, coniugi
                    <lb n="3"/>dulcissimae.
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>To <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicria Eutychis</persName>. <persName ref="#heracleon" xml:lang="la">Cicrius Heracleon</persName>, to his sweetest wife.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                <p>A <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicria Eutychis</persName>. <persName ref="#heracleon" xml:lang="la">Cicrius Heracleon</persName>, alla dolcissima moglie.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>The sarcophagus of <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicria Eutychis</persName> was commissioned by her husband <persName ref="#heracleon" xml:lang="la">Cicrius Heracleon</persName>. Unlike the burial of <ref target="./eutychiana.xml"><persName xml:lang="la">Eutychiana</persName></ref>, here the parents do not join the husband as dedicators.</p>
                <p>It is possible that <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicria Eutychis</persName>, unlike her sister, died after her parents, which would explain their absence from the inscription.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="it">
                <p>L’arca di <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicria Eutychis</persName> viene commissionata dal marito <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicrius Heracleon</persName>. A differenza della sepoltura di <ref target="./eutychiana.xml"><persName xml:lang="la">Eutychiana</persName></ref>, qui i genitori non si uniscono al marito come dedicanti.</p>
                <p>Forse <persName ref="#eutychis" xml:lang="la">Cicria Eutychis</persName>, a differenza della sorella, è morta dopo i suoi genitori, il che spiegherebbe la loro assenza nell'epigrafe.</p>
            </div>
